Description: Provides tools to estimate health inequality metrics using grouped 
    ecological data. The package implements the estimation of the Absolute Gap (AG), 
    Relative Gap (RG), Absolute Concentration Index (ACI), Relative Concentration 
    Index (RCI), Slope Index of Inequality (SII), and Relative Index of Inequality 
    (RII). It supports complex grouped-data modeling, nonlinear back-transformations,
    bounded-outcome corrections (Wagstaff and Erreygers), and extensive uncertainty
    quantification through analytical variance approximation and resampling techniques 
    (Bootstrap and Jackknife).
